WEBVTT

00:01.202 --> 00:03.104
Previously on The Unit.
[ Jonas ]
He's not breathing.

00:03.137 --> 00:04.872
Forgive me, Father,
for I have sinned.

00:04.905 --> 00:08.376
- What are they?
- They're the burdens
you carry here.

00:08.409 --> 00:12.012
Look. I just got my wife back.
I ain't gonna lose her again.

00:12.046 --> 00:15.316
- Welcome to the Unit, Sergeant.
- Staff Sergeant McBride,
meet Warrant Officer Sullivan.

00:15.349 --> 00:17.851
- I didn't know there were
women in the Unit.
- [ Mack ] There aren't.

00:17.885 --> 00:20.754
Whoa. What are you--
What are you doing?
You're right. I'm sorry.

00:20.788 --> 00:21.755
Don't give it another thought.

00:44.778 --> 00:46.680
[ Jonas ]
They took the bait.
[ Chattering ]

00:48.549 --> 00:50.484
That's him.

00:51.352 --> 00:54.122
Steady.
The wind shifted.

00:59.627 --> 01:02.896
[ Chattering ]

01:02.930 --> 01:05.032
Target's green.
[ Jonas On Earpiece ]
Team ready?

01:05.065 --> 01:06.467
[ Mack ]
Ready.
[ Bob ] Ready.

01:06.500 --> 01:08.136
[ Jonas ]
In five.

01:11.605 --> 01:14.074
[ Gunshots ]

01:18.679 --> 01:20.581
Put it down!

01:24.051 --> 01:25.586
Daniel Miller?

01:25.619 --> 01:27.455
[ Speaking Arabic ]

01:27.488 --> 01:29.623
Things you learn
in the Philadelphia
public school system.

01:29.657 --> 01:32.826
Your family's been
looking for you.
My family wishes I was dead.

01:32.860 --> 01:36.230
Not your uncle.
Your Uncle Sam sent us for you.

01:36.264 --> 01:38.098
You won't make it
out of this canyon alive.

01:38.132 --> 01:40.834
You'll be shot down like dogs.

01:42.503 --> 01:44.438
Get in!

02:01.189 --> 02:05.626
You're alone, outmanned,
under armed.

02:05.659 --> 02:07.428
And we are legion.

02:07.461 --> 02:09.863
- We have sarin gas.
We have anthrax.
- [ Fighter Jet Approaching ]

02:20.040 --> 02:21.342
You take my point?

02:27.415 --> 02:29.116
Americans in action.

02:29.149 --> 02:32.253
Hear, hear.
Hear, hear.

02:36.990 --> 02:38.492
What is this, a race?

02:39.493 --> 02:41.429
You got a decade
head start on me.

02:41.462 --> 02:43.264
- [ Laughs ]
- Really?

02:46.800 --> 02:48.636
Another round?

02:48.669 --> 02:51.004
Uh, mission briefs.
Mission briefs?

02:51.038 --> 02:52.840
What is that?
Like a thong?

02:52.873 --> 02:55.276
- [ Bridget ]
Oh!
- Oh, God.

02:55.309 --> 02:57.144
Oh, boy.
You know what? Um--
Come on.

02:57.177 --> 02:59.580
- This girl's turning in.
Good night.
- Good night.

02:59.613 --> 03:01.349
- I was joking.
- This boy too.

03:01.382 --> 03:03.183
What time's your mom
want you home?

03:03.217 --> 03:05.185
Road trip with the wife,
first light.

03:05.219 --> 03:06.720
Hands on the wheel
at all times, Sergeant.

03:06.754 --> 03:08.722
Sorry.
Last message not received.

03:08.756 --> 03:10.258
[ Snickers ]

03:12.260 --> 03:14.228
You guys can go.
I got this.

03:14.262 --> 03:15.796
[ Bob ]
Yeah?
Yeah.

03:15.829 --> 03:18.699
** [ Speakers: Pop ]
** [ Man Singing, Indistinct ]

03:19.800 --> 03:21.635
Hey.
Hi.

03:21.669 --> 03:23.637
- I thought you left.
- Oh, I'm leaving now.

03:23.671 --> 03:26.640
You know what I could use?
A ride home.

03:26.674 --> 03:28.842
Maybe a place to crash
for the night.

03:28.876 --> 03:32.112
How does that sound?
It sounds like
it's not gonna happen.

03:32.145 --> 03:35.549
Well, we could do this.
We could have
a few more drinks--

03:35.583 --> 03:38.018
Hey, listen.
You're at a tactical
disadvantage, mister.

03:38.051 --> 03:40.321
I'm not interested.

03:40.354 --> 03:42.890
And you're way off base.

03:42.923 --> 03:45.092
Let me say
one more thing.
Hey, hey, hey.

03:45.125 --> 03:46.894
You're new.
So you get one warning.

03:46.927 --> 03:49.363
One warning.
And this is
your warning.

03:49.397 --> 03:51.465
Knock it off.
All right?

03:51.499 --> 03:53.434
Bob--
Go exercise your charm
somewhere else.

03:54.768 --> 03:56.704
Briefing at 0700.

04:03.977 --> 04:05.846
[ Car Alarm Chirps ]

04:08.449 --> 04:11.385
- [ Sam ]
Hey.
- Pal, seriously.

04:11.419 --> 04:13.354
I want to apologize.
Do it tomorrow.

04:13.387 --> 04:15.889
I worked it out.
It's good.

04:15.923 --> 04:19.360
Would you do me the honor
of hearing my apology?

04:19.393 --> 04:20.994
Tomorrow. Go home.

04:23.531 --> 04:27.200
It's hard for me to meet women
I don't work with.

04:27.234 --> 04:29.570
I mean, I can't exactly
take out an ad.

04:29.603 --> 04:32.440
"Six foot, blue eyes,
kills for a living."

04:32.473 --> 04:34.508
Take your self-pity
and sleep it off.

04:35.609 --> 04:37.745
I can't sleep
until I make this right.

04:37.778 --> 04:40.748
Okay. Whether
you sleep or not
is of no concern to me.

04:42.450 --> 04:45.152
- I guess I'm just confused.
- Really?

04:45.185 --> 04:47.488
I keep hearing
you're on the team.

04:47.521 --> 04:49.757
You're not on the team.
You're just visiting.

04:49.790 --> 04:52.426
You don't belong here.
That is fascinating.

04:52.460 --> 04:55.796
But pathetic, pal, okay?
How dense are you?

04:55.829 --> 04:58.466
No, no, no, no, no.
I want-- I want to
get this straight.

04:58.499 --> 05:01.101
You're not one of us, right?

05:01.134 --> 05:04.705
Oh, you help out,
but you're not a shooter.

05:04.738 --> 05:07.007
So the rules
don't apply to you.

05:07.040 --> 05:09.843
So that means the rules
don't apply to me.

05:09.877 --> 05:11.879
Sam!

05:11.912 --> 05:13.914
Shh.
Sam!

05:13.947 --> 05:15.849
Sam, what the hell?

05:15.883 --> 05:17.951
- Shut up for a second.
- [ Muffled Shouting ]

05:18.886 --> 05:20.788
[ Sam Groans ]

05:24.592 --> 05:27.661
[ Bridget Groans ]
All right.

05:28.929 --> 05:31.599
- Didn't want to do it this way.
- [ Groans ]

05:33.166 --> 05:34.334
[ Groans ]

05:34.368 --> 05:36.404
[ Screams ]

05:39.773 --> 05:41.909
[ Screams ]

05:41.942 --> 05:43.844
[ Man ]
Hello?

05:43.877 --> 05:45.846
What's goin' on?

05:45.879 --> 05:48.048
I saw him. I saw him.
Oh, my God.

05:48.081 --> 05:50.050
- Are you all right?
I'll call 911.
- No.

05:50.951 --> 05:53.186
I'm okay.
Thank you.

05:53.220 --> 05:55.088
I'm fine.

05:56.223 --> 05:58.025
- I'm okay.
- But--

05:58.058 --> 05:59.560
I'm okay.

06:03.564 --> 06:05.466
The subject is
confirmed inside.

06:05.499 --> 06:08.135
When Charlie team reports
affirmative, we'll proceed
to condition green--

06:08.168 --> 06:10.738
- [ Door Opens ]
- where Alpha team
will activate...

06:10.771 --> 06:13.474
- Operation Indigo Blizzard.
- [ Door Closes ]

06:15.342 --> 06:18.011
You got something
on your face.

06:18.045 --> 06:20.247
No. I, uh--
[ Clears Throat ]
lost a barbell this morning.

06:20.280 --> 06:22.349
[ Ryan ]
Good morning, Warrant Officer.

06:22.382 --> 06:25.719
- I'm sure your watch is slow.
- Sir, I've adjusted it.
Thank you, sir.

06:26.820 --> 06:29.089
Sergeant Major,
you're still short one man.

06:29.122 --> 06:33.226
Yes, sir. And when I see
Sergeant McBride, I will make
the appropriate corrective.

06:33.260 --> 06:35.996
Operation Indigo Blizzard,
sir.

06:40.100 --> 06:44.204
Operation Indigo Blizzard
calls for eight men
plus support PAX.

06:44.237 --> 06:47.107
You'll get an in-country
through friendlies
in the Port of Augustus.

06:47.140 --> 06:50.511
Meet up with your contacts
in a farmhouse 70 klicks
to the southwest.

06:50.544 --> 06:53.246
The farmhouse owner
will be paid
at your discretion.

06:53.280 --> 06:57.150
Now, we've used this guy before,
but he's gonna keep
his hands open.

06:57.184 --> 06:59.252
Sergeant Major,
does your team
need the room?

06:59.286 --> 07:01.188
Yes, sir.

07:01.221 --> 07:02.856
Thank you, sir.

07:07.394 --> 07:08.629
[ Door Opens ]

07:12.533 --> 07:16.103
- Look at me.
- We should resume the briefing.

07:16.136 --> 07:17.771
Say the words.

07:19.740 --> 07:22.442
He surprised me at my car.

07:23.977 --> 07:26.279
He threw me down.

07:26.313 --> 07:28.181
He tried to rape me.

07:34.454 --> 07:36.524
Say the name.

07:40.193 --> 07:41.529
Sam.

07:45.298 --> 07:47.935
Cool Breeze, you're with me.

07:58.345 --> 08:00.748
Open this door now, Sergeant.

08:11.559 --> 08:13.460
Go bag's gone.

08:13.493 --> 08:15.529
Ditched his wallet
and his phone.

08:15.563 --> 08:17.698
Stupid.

08:17.731 --> 08:20.668
- No calls out since 3:00 a.m.
- He's bugged out.

08:20.701 --> 08:23.571
Inform the TOC.
Kill his passports
and hideaways.

08:23.604 --> 08:26.774
Flash his vitals to F.B.I.,
N.T.S.B., D.H.S.

08:26.807 --> 08:28.408
Roger.

08:28.441 --> 08:30.443
Where is he?

08:30.477 --> 08:33.881
Hasn't had time to build up
assets or networks,
and he can't use ours.

08:33.914 --> 08:36.550
He's either hitchhiking
out of town--

08:36.584 --> 08:38.185
Or he's still here,
holed up with friendlies.

08:38.218 --> 08:41.722
Get me the contacts
out of that thing.
Give me a list of most likelies.

08:43.523 --> 08:45.859
I need that list now.

08:51.231 --> 08:53.033
What's that look?

08:53.066 --> 08:54.802
He's trained
to evade an army.

08:54.835 --> 08:57.404
I helped train him.
I know what he's trained for.

08:57.437 --> 08:59.539
I'm gonna bring his ass back.

09:02.275 --> 09:05.946
[ Man ]
* Give me your secrets
Bring me a sign *

09:05.979 --> 09:09.717
* Give me a reason
to walk the fire *

09:09.750 --> 09:12.686
* See another dawn

09:12.720 --> 09:14.287
* Through a daughter's eyes

09:14.321 --> 09:18.892
* You give me a reason
to walk the fire **

09:26.466 --> 09:30.003
No. I-I appreciate the absence
of the M.P.'s. I appreciate
the Unit handling this itself.

09:30.037 --> 09:32.906
I just want to know,
why did Jonas go alone?

09:32.940 --> 09:36.443
Look. Sam is trained
to spot surveillance
and pursuit.

09:36.476 --> 09:40.347
We use this training to identify
our enemies, whether it's, uh,
counterintelligence...

09:40.380 --> 09:43.784
or antimilitary strike teams,
before they act.

09:43.817 --> 09:46.720
They labor so hard
to make themselves
invisible,

09:46.754 --> 09:49.757
to make everything
appear normal,

09:49.790 --> 09:52.292
that the absence
of the abnormal
gives them away.

09:52.325 --> 09:56.229
So, in Sam's case, if we send
five, six, 12 guys after him,

09:56.263 --> 09:58.666
we might as well send
a marching band
and a drum major.

09:58.699 --> 10:00.133
Yes. Of course.

10:00.167 --> 10:03.804
So, as Jonas says,
it's a mission
for a thousand men.

10:03.837 --> 10:06.206
- Or one.
- Mm-hmm. That's right.

10:06.239 --> 10:08.208
Okay.

10:12.045 --> 10:14.948
Soldier, it's time you and I
had a conversation.

10:14.982 --> 10:19.019
An injury report is required
for this investigation.

10:19.052 --> 10:21.922
Sir, I don't want
an investigation.
I don't recall asking you.

10:21.955 --> 10:24.357
Sir, I don't want this
on my record.

10:24.391 --> 10:26.559
I don't want to be the victim.

10:26.593 --> 10:30.898
Understood.
Now get yourself
down to the med shed.

10:30.931 --> 10:33.233
Yes, sir.
[ Door Closes ]

10:39.572 --> 10:42.475
Where do you think you're going?
You gonna hold my hair back?

10:42.509 --> 10:46.980
Look. I should've landed on the
guy when I saw him step out of
line. I should've stepped in.

10:47.014 --> 10:50.183
Look. You're not the rapist,
and you're not the victim.

10:50.217 --> 10:53.120
So just relax
and enjoy the show.

10:54.487 --> 10:56.389
Thank you.

10:59.459 --> 11:01.361
[ Door Closes ]

11:04.597 --> 11:06.734
[ Crow Squawks ]

11:09.169 --> 11:11.805
This place is old enough
to be Lincoln's summer home.

11:11.839 --> 11:14.141
Yeah, but it's got
character.

11:14.174 --> 11:17.711
Well, if you're interested
in keeping the place,
you'll want these.

11:17.745 --> 11:19.913
These outline
the various taxes and fees.

11:19.947 --> 11:22.783
You sign this deed,
have these notarized,

11:22.816 --> 11:26.553
and per the terms of your
husband's great-aunt's will,
the house is yours.

11:26.586 --> 11:28.288
[ Cell Phone Rings ]
Excuse me.

11:30.457 --> 11:33.460
You know what we struck?

11:33.493 --> 11:36.229
We struck gold.

11:36.263 --> 11:39.099
I didn't know gold
came in anything this small.
Okay.

11:39.132 --> 11:42.635
So it's cozy. But see here.
It's got a great front porch.

11:42.669 --> 11:45.372
The master bedroom
gets morning light,

11:45.405 --> 11:48.308
and there's a shed in the back
for whatever it is
that men do in sheds.

11:48.341 --> 11:51.745
It's tempting. The plumbing
is a biblical disaster.

11:51.779 --> 11:53.646
The girls would have to
share a bedroom.

11:53.680 --> 11:57.317
The girls share a room now.
Look. We could make a home here.

11:57.350 --> 11:58.886
What's your objection?

11:58.919 --> 12:01.421
You can't say
the money's not right.

12:01.454 --> 12:04.557
Sweetie,
I wish I could see it.
The nearest base is--

12:04.591 --> 12:06.126
I'm talking about
after the army.

12:06.159 --> 12:07.828
And when is that, precisely?

12:07.861 --> 12:11.064
I'm not rushing you.

12:11.098 --> 12:14.601
But someday, we're gonna
have to jump off that train.

12:14.634 --> 12:17.137
And we could land here.

12:17.170 --> 12:19.907
Think of it as an exit strategy.
We deserve it.

12:21.641 --> 12:23.811
I deserve to know
that it's here.

12:24.945 --> 12:26.980
We don't have to decide
everything now, do we?

12:27.014 --> 12:29.749
Will you consider it?

12:30.984 --> 12:34.187
Will you?
I'm considering
considering it.

12:34.221 --> 12:36.857
All right.
That's good enough for me.

12:55.976 --> 12:58.678
I didn't know anybody was here.

12:58.711 --> 13:00.613
I haven't been
for a long time.

13:00.647 --> 13:03.450
What brings you back?

13:03.483 --> 13:05.285
Well, what usually brings
people back to church?

13:05.318 --> 13:08.421
So, naturally,
you've come to
beg forgiveness?

13:08.455 --> 13:11.624
I don't know if begging
will do the trick.
I got a lot to answer for.

13:11.658 --> 13:12.893
Like what?

13:14.895 --> 13:17.364
Well, vandalism for starters.

13:17.397 --> 13:19.632
Mack Gerhardt,

13:19.666 --> 13:23.670
age 10,
carved his name into a seat.

13:23.703 --> 13:25.873
Was that an act of vandalism?

13:25.906 --> 13:28.075
What else you call it?

13:28.108 --> 13:30.510
A desire to be remembered.

13:30.543 --> 13:32.779
That's why you came back too.

13:32.812 --> 13:35.949
- Why is that, ma'am?
- To see if there's still
a remembrance of you...

13:35.983 --> 13:38.785
in church.
Is that true?

13:38.818 --> 13:41.989
Well, you know it's true.

13:44.591 --> 13:47.560
Did you come back
to apologize for something?

13:49.662 --> 13:52.032
[ Mack Sighs ]

13:52.065 --> 13:54.401
Is that why people
come back to church?

13:54.434 --> 13:56.870
Yes. As I understand it.

13:56.904 --> 13:59.339
I thought they came
to pray for guidance.

13:59.372 --> 14:02.109
Nobody prays for guidance
because they've done right.

14:02.142 --> 14:04.277
You ever hear of that?

14:04.311 --> 14:06.379
I don't know...

14:08.648 --> 14:10.650
if I believe in God.

14:10.683 --> 14:13.186
You confused?

14:15.889 --> 14:19.459
-Yeah.
-And do you think that somewhere
there is understanding?

14:24.631 --> 14:27.867
I don't know.
Would you like
there to be?

14:29.869 --> 14:32.472
Yes.

14:32.505 --> 14:35.075
That's what it means
to believe in God.

14:35.108 --> 14:37.210
That's all it means.

14:38.378 --> 14:41.982
I've done so many
bad things in my life.

14:42.015 --> 14:44.351
So have I.

14:48.255 --> 14:50.357
You?

14:51.858 --> 14:53.927
What have you done?

14:53.961 --> 14:57.164
Well--
[ Clears Throat ]
my daughter died.

14:57.197 --> 15:01.401
Sorry.
It's a long time ago.

15:01.434 --> 15:03.003
How old was she?

15:03.036 --> 15:05.572
She died three hours
before she was born.

15:05.605 --> 15:08.241
I'm so sorry.
Mmm.

15:08.275 --> 15:12.179
I didn't know how to go on
without my beautiful baby girl.

15:12.212 --> 15:14.814
My husband couldn't go on.

15:14.847 --> 15:17.017
I asked God for answers,

15:17.050 --> 15:19.119
but he didn't give me any.

15:19.152 --> 15:24.324
And so?
So I did something about it.
I decided,

15:24.357 --> 15:28.695
rather than to bother God,
I'd do something myself.

15:28.728 --> 15:30.397
What'd you do?

15:31.531 --> 15:33.700
I found another one.

15:44.978 --> 15:46.846
[ Gasps ]
Sam. Is he inside?

15:46.879 --> 15:49.782
[ Muffled Murmur ]
Okay.
I'm not here to hurt you.

15:49.816 --> 15:52.452
I've come for Sam.
If he's inside,

15:52.485 --> 15:55.022
if he's come to you
for help,
you might nod.

15:56.956 --> 15:59.692
Open the door.

16:01.494 --> 16:03.430
Sit down.

16:04.664 --> 16:06.566
Who are you?

16:08.201 --> 16:11.338
He's not here.
I haven't seen him
in months.

16:11.371 --> 16:13.473
And he called you this morning?

16:13.506 --> 16:15.775
Yes.

16:15.808 --> 16:18.278
You his girlfriend?
Ex.

16:18.311 --> 16:21.114
- What'd he say to you?
- Nothing.

16:21.148 --> 16:23.083
Oh, he said something.
He wasn't making any sense.

16:23.116 --> 16:26.386
He's gonna need cash, I.D.'s,
transportation and friends.
What'd he ask you for?

16:26.419 --> 16:28.688
We're not friends.
Oh, you're not?

16:28.721 --> 16:31.224
He got a new assignment,
and he started acting strange
right after that.

16:31.258 --> 16:33.326
He's acting strange.

16:34.994 --> 16:36.863
He's got a place...

16:36.896 --> 16:39.532
where he keeps everything
he needs in an emergency.

16:39.566 --> 16:41.901
Can you think of
a place like that?

16:41.934 --> 16:43.570
Tell me.

16:43.603 --> 16:47.207
He and his buddies
keep a storage locker,
somewhere up north.

16:48.641 --> 16:51.611
- Is he gonna be all right?
- I don't see how.

16:54.414 --> 16:56.983
You're not the pastor,
are you?
[ Door Opens ]

16:57.016 --> 16:59.786
No.

16:59.819 --> 17:01.821
Who are you?

17:01.854 --> 17:03.923
My name is Nora.

17:03.956 --> 17:07.860
I'm Mack.
Nora, this is my wife, Tiffy.

17:07.894 --> 17:09.829
Tiffy, this is Nora.
Hi, Nora.

17:09.862 --> 17:14.134
My wife found me at church.
She must have looked
everywhere else first.

17:14.167 --> 17:16.703
That's right.

17:16.736 --> 17:18.938
Why'd you tell me
you were the pastor, Nora?

17:18.971 --> 17:20.940
I never said
I was the pastor.

17:20.973 --> 17:23.976
You said your daughter died
and so you found another one.

17:24.010 --> 17:26.846
That's right.
How'd you find another baby?

17:26.879 --> 17:29.015
She found another baby?

17:29.048 --> 17:30.750
I explained it to you.

17:30.783 --> 17:34.454
That's right.
You explained it,
and then you told me about God.

17:34.487 --> 17:36.223
Yes.

17:37.857 --> 17:40.427
You came here to speak
to someone, didn't you?

17:40.460 --> 17:42.395
Yes. To speak to the pastor.

17:42.429 --> 17:44.131
Maybe you can speak to me.

17:46.399 --> 17:49.702
Why you?
Well, you said
you believe in God, right?

17:49.736 --> 17:51.304
Maybe God sent me here.

17:53.740 --> 17:55.342
Are you a nurse?

17:55.375 --> 17:57.344
No.

17:57.377 --> 18:00.012
I went to the hospital.

18:00.046 --> 18:02.182
I went in a room.

18:02.215 --> 18:04.251
This woman had
a baby girl last night.

18:04.284 --> 18:06.253
I told her
how lucky she was.

18:06.286 --> 18:08.721
Then I put on the lab coat,

18:08.755 --> 18:12.659
and I walked past
the nurses' station
at the shift change.

18:12.692 --> 18:15.628
I went to the mother.
I told her I was a doctor.

18:15.662 --> 18:19.599
And I told her a phrase
that I'd practiced all day.

18:21.168 --> 18:24.471
"We've detected
a bacterial infection,

18:24.504 --> 18:26.473
and we need to test her
for sepsis."

18:29.108 --> 18:31.711
She handed me her baby.

18:31.744 --> 18:35.248
And I took my new baby,
and we walked out.

18:35.282 --> 18:37.750
Where's the baby now?

20:21.854 --> 20:23.390
[ Vehicle Approaching ]

20:32.365 --> 20:33.966
[ Chattering ]
Yeah.

20:43.175 --> 20:44.444
Oh, no.

20:51.050 --> 20:52.319
Son of a gun.

20:55.187 --> 20:57.357
Who packed
this thing in here?

22:15.835 --> 22:17.003
[ Gun Cocks ]

22:17.036 --> 22:19.305
Well, that was fast.

22:19.338 --> 22:22.642
- Put the gun down.
- Whatever she said,
it's not how it happened.

22:22.675 --> 22:24.877
- Explain it from the pavement.
- I didn't mean to push her.

22:24.911 --> 22:28.280
The only reason I did
was I needed to keep her quiet.
Please.

22:28.314 --> 22:31.651
Let the man go,
put the gun down
and get on the ground.

22:31.684 --> 22:33.453
I didn't mean
for this to happen.

22:33.486 --> 22:35.187
It's over, Sergeant.
It's all over.

22:35.221 --> 22:36.789
Not like this.

22:36.823 --> 22:38.391
You better take cover,
Jonas.

22:38.425 --> 22:39.892
[ Clink ]

22:39.926 --> 22:40.727
[ Grunts ]

22:45.432 --> 22:47.467
You all right?

22:48.801 --> 22:51.538
Sam, I don't want to shoot you.

23:01.948 --> 23:04.050
[ Chattering ]

23:04.083 --> 23:05.785
Whoa. Hey.

23:05.818 --> 23:07.386
- [ Chattering ]
- [ Man ]
Crazy.

23:09.489 --> 23:12.759
[ Groaning ]
[ Bone Cracks ]

23:12.792 --> 23:14.894
Are you okay?
Hey. Wait a minute.
Wait. Wait.

23:16.362 --> 23:18.731
Oh, my God.
Are you all right?

23:22.201 --> 23:24.103
[ Woman Whimpers ]

23:24.136 --> 23:26.372
- Move.
- [ Man ] Get out.
Everyone get out.

23:26.405 --> 23:28.274
[ Woman ]
Check the break room!

23:28.307 --> 23:31.177
[ Man ]
Call the police!
Sam!

23:31.210 --> 23:32.411
Sam!

23:34.380 --> 23:36.949
[ Women Shouting ]

23:36.983 --> 23:38.918
Stay back!

23:43.155 --> 23:45.157
[ Doorknob Rattles ]

23:45.191 --> 23:47.126
It's not like she said, Jonas.

23:47.159 --> 23:50.429
I don't care what it's like.
Open the door.
I would have come in--

23:50.463 --> 23:53.466
eventually.
[ Sirens Wailing ]

23:53.500 --> 23:56.869
I wanted some time to think!
Is that insane--
that I wanted time to think?

23:56.903 --> 23:59.038
You're gonna get a lot of it.

23:59.071 --> 24:00.540
[ Sirens Continue ]

24:05.044 --> 24:06.245
Stay back, pal!

24:06.278 --> 24:08.915
Stay back!

24:08.948 --> 24:11.217
Or I'll shoot!

24:14.687 --> 24:16.656
Next one's going
into something soft.

24:18.290 --> 24:20.092
All right. All right!

24:21.994 --> 24:25.464
Nora, tell us
where the baby is.

24:25.498 --> 24:29.168
- I--
- Tell us where the baby is.
Is the baby with you?

24:29.201 --> 24:31.303
No.
Where is she?

24:31.337 --> 24:33.706
- Is she alive?
- Yes. She's alive.

24:33.740 --> 24:35.875
Is she safe?
Yes, but--

24:35.908 --> 24:39.278
- But what?
- I'm not sure.

24:39.311 --> 24:41.313
Do you understand?

24:41.347 --> 24:44.551
- That God wants me
to give the baby back.
- [ Man ] Who's in here?

24:47.787 --> 24:49.856
[ Whispers ]
I'm a federal officer.

24:49.889 --> 24:51.924
What's the church doing open?

24:51.958 --> 24:53.926
Isn't the pastor here?
The pastor's on vacation.

24:53.960 --> 24:56.328
- What are you doing here?
- I'm just rattling doorknobs.

24:56.362 --> 24:59.298
Hey. That's the girl that
took the kid from the hospital.
That's right. That's right.

24:59.331 --> 25:02.201
You've got the child?
The child's not with her.
I'm gettin' to her.

25:02.234 --> 25:04.837
Just leave me with her
for 10 minutes
and I'll find the child.

25:04.871 --> 25:07.473
How?

25:07.506 --> 25:09.809
She's talking to me.

25:09.842 --> 25:11.678
[ Man ]
Well, why is she
talking to you?

25:11.711 --> 25:13.713
I'll be damned if I know,
but she is.

25:16.115 --> 25:18.751
You just made detective.
Call your sergeant.

25:20.119 --> 25:22.121
You got till
my sergeant gets here.

25:27.894 --> 25:29.896
[ Door Opens, Closes ]

25:31.230 --> 25:34.667
She'll tell the pastor
where the baby is.

25:34.701 --> 25:37.804
Well, that's good.
Thank you, Nora.

25:37.837 --> 25:39.606
Because the pastor
will know what to do.

25:39.639 --> 25:41.340
That's right. She will.

25:41.373 --> 25:44.410
Because the baby
may need some care.
[ Mack ] Of course she does.

25:44.443 --> 25:47.279
- She needs her medicine.
- [ Mack ]
Of course.

25:47.313 --> 25:49.649
We should see she gets it.

25:52.018 --> 25:56.388
SWAT's probably gonna go
straight through that front
door, maybe from over the top.

25:56.422 --> 26:01.160
Lieutenant, think about
anything but posse comitatus
for the next hour.

26:01.193 --> 26:03.395
We're just two locals
with something in common.

26:03.429 --> 26:05.898
Tell us where
you want us, Colonel.
Secure yourselves a flight down.

26:05.932 --> 26:07.867
We'll bring you up
if it comes to that.

26:07.900 --> 26:10.069
[ Helicopter Whirring Overhead ]

26:11.704 --> 26:13.740
Time is not our friend, Jonas.

26:13.773 --> 26:15.875
We can't keep these cameras
in the dark for long.

26:15.908 --> 26:18.344
Too many witnesses
saw him come through here.

26:18.377 --> 26:20.279
His cover's not gonna hold.
We gotta close this down.

26:20.312 --> 26:22.281
He's talking and not shooting.
That's a start.

26:22.314 --> 26:24.250
- No. He's lost it.
- I can talk him out.
- Can you?

26:24.283 --> 26:26.385
- Yes.
- I want him alive.
- Yes, sir.

26:26.418 --> 26:28.420
But if he endangers the public,

26:28.454 --> 26:30.389
you have a green light
to terminate.

26:30.422 --> 26:33.025
Sam knows what'll happen to him
if he takes another shot.

26:33.059 --> 26:35.194
I can talk him down.
But if I can't,

26:35.227 --> 26:37.664
those guys down there--
they don't notch him.

26:37.697 --> 26:41.367
The adjacent building
has an unobstructed view
into the office.

26:41.400 --> 26:44.170
High enough for a vantage,
and if necessary, a shot.

26:44.203 --> 26:46.305
I'll go.
I'll get my kit and set up.

26:46.338 --> 26:48.975
- I hear you talking.
Ticktock.
- Yeah.

26:56.515 --> 26:58.818
[ Beeps ]
[ Man ]
Get back!

27:00.352 --> 27:02.354
[ Phone Rings ]
[ Male Reporter ]
In Greenwood,

27:02.388 --> 27:04.423
we have reports of shots fired
at a car dealership.

27:04.456 --> 27:08.227
We have Ted at the scene.
Ted, what do you have for us?
Hello?

27:08.260 --> 27:09.762
Hey. It's me.
Sam.

27:09.796 --> 27:11.798
Where are you?
Are you okay?

27:11.831 --> 27:13.700
I guess you're not
watching the news.

27:13.733 --> 27:15.702
[ Male Reporter ]
...holed himself up
in the manager's office.

27:15.735 --> 27:19.739
This is you? Shooting at people?

27:19.772 --> 27:21.841
You're gonna hear things
about me that aren't true.

27:21.874 --> 27:24.811
They may even try to pretend
this never happened.

27:25.812 --> 27:27.814
Well, you tell them...

27:27.847 --> 27:30.616
that Sam McBride
was a good soldier.

27:30.649 --> 27:32.785
Oh, my God, Sam. Ple--

27:32.819 --> 27:36.588
Don't let 'em forget.
[ Beeps ]

27:36.622 --> 27:38.324
[ Reporter ]
Officials are on scene.

27:38.357 --> 27:41.027
[ Sighs ]

27:44.096 --> 27:46.265
What would you like to do,
Sergeant?

27:46.298 --> 27:49.736
This is the part
where the hostile
asks for a helicopter.

27:50.636 --> 27:52.905
Well, let's skip ahead.

27:52.939 --> 27:55.775
Go ahead and tell me
how it was all
a misunderstanding.

27:56.809 --> 27:58.878
Well--
Start changing the facts.

27:58.911 --> 28:03.515
- Open the door.
- All I wanted to be
was an operator.

28:03.549 --> 28:06.418
You were, Sam.
Hell of an operator.

28:07.887 --> 28:11.123
I saw your legs finally
got away from you.

28:11.157 --> 28:13.860
Yeah. Yeah.

28:15.061 --> 28:17.096
How's the ankle?
Perfect.

28:17.129 --> 28:19.799
- I heal fast.
- Why don't you let me
get a look at it?

28:19.832 --> 28:22.969
You could give me 15 minutes.

28:23.002 --> 28:26.806
Fifteen minutes alone--
to think.

28:26.839 --> 28:28.775
And then all this would be over.

28:28.808 --> 28:30.910
Can't do it, Sergeant.

28:32.444 --> 28:34.380
It's the best way.

28:34.413 --> 28:38.184
It's safer.
You come for me,
I will shoot.

28:40.052 --> 28:42.621
- You saw the box in my locker?
- Yeah, I saw it.

28:42.654 --> 28:44.490
Well, it's lightened since then.

28:45.858 --> 28:49.661
I'm showing your sniper--
Is it Bob?

28:49.695 --> 28:52.865
I'm showing him
a concussion grenade.

28:52.899 --> 28:56.068
Confirmed.
One concussion grenade.

28:56.102 --> 28:58.771
I'm three corners
blind and red.
Repeat. I have no shot.

28:58.805 --> 29:00.940
Okay.

29:00.973 --> 29:03.776
There's three more
he can't see.
You read me?

29:03.810 --> 29:06.712
Yeah. I read you.

29:06.745 --> 29:08.815
You try to come through
that door, Jonas,

29:09.816 --> 29:11.818
you can call it
the Fourth of July.

29:19.826 --> 29:24.396
Details are scarce, but
a woman identifying herself as
the suspect's ex-girlfriend...

29:24.430 --> 29:28.234
has confirmed the gunman
as Samuel Simmons McBride,

29:28.267 --> 29:31.270
a second-year member
of the U.S. Army
Logistical Studies Unit.

29:31.303 --> 29:33.339
And there it is.

29:33.372 --> 29:37.009
The suspect was witnessed
brandishing a firearm
in several locations...

29:37.043 --> 29:40.612
prior to barricading himself
in the car dealership behind me.

29:40.646 --> 29:42.614
Colonel, news has him I.D.'d.

29:42.648 --> 29:45.852
Thank you, Sergeant.
[ Beeps ]

29:45.885 --> 29:48.554
[ Man ] Do you have any further
information on the gunman?
I've heard enough.

29:48.587 --> 29:51.157
Show me new business.
Sure.

29:51.190 --> 29:54.393
Bring up
Operation Valentine Cross
and update sat image.

29:54.426 --> 29:57.329
For our own safety,
we're being kept at a distance.

29:57.363 --> 29:58.397
We're told negoti--

30:00.466 --> 30:02.969
Clock's run out, Jonas.

30:03.002 --> 30:05.637
Any means necessary
that avoids civilian casualties.

30:05.671 --> 30:07.806
All right.

30:10.676 --> 30:12.678
Lieutenant.

30:12.711 --> 30:15.047
Bring 'em up.

30:20.286 --> 30:23.789
Copy that.
Kid's gotta have
epinephrine on the hour.

30:23.822 --> 30:25.591
She's got the meds.

30:25.624 --> 30:28.027
[ Sirens Wailing ]

30:28.060 --> 30:30.462
But you must have taken
the baby with you.

30:30.496 --> 30:33.732
Did you take the baby with you?
I'd like to tell you.
You know I would.

30:33.765 --> 30:36.502
Nora, we need to
find the child.

30:36.535 --> 30:39.038
The pastor's coming.
I'll tell the pastor.

30:39.071 --> 30:41.607
The pastor has been delayed.
The pastor's not here, Nora.

30:43.943 --> 30:46.545
When you came here,
the church was locked.

30:46.578 --> 30:48.747
That's right.
I broke in.

30:48.780 --> 30:51.850
And what did you do
with the child?
It wasn't with me.

30:51.884 --> 30:54.453
- Why not?
- I was afraid.

30:54.486 --> 30:57.223
- Yes?
- That the pastor
would take it from me.

30:57.256 --> 31:00.092
Why would she
take it from you?

31:00.126 --> 31:01.827
If it was the right
thing to do.

31:01.860 --> 31:04.897
If she said it was
the right thing to do,
then you'd give her the child.

31:04.931 --> 31:07.033
If sh said.

31:07.066 --> 31:10.069
Why?
Because it would be
the word of God.

31:10.102 --> 31:11.971
- Nora, the police are coming.
- I won't tell them.

31:12.004 --> 31:14.606
I will only tell
a person of God.

31:37.429 --> 31:39.365
Nora.

31:40.699 --> 31:42.568
Nora, I am a man of God.

31:42.601 --> 31:45.972
God sent me here, Nora,
to be with you.

31:46.905 --> 31:49.008
How do I know that?

31:50.242 --> 31:52.444
Who else would've
sent me, Nora?

31:54.146 --> 31:57.083
Do you believe in God?

31:57.116 --> 31:58.985
Do you believe
God sent you?

31:59.018 --> 32:01.653
I know it.

32:01.687 --> 32:03.755
Why?

32:03.789 --> 32:05.624
To save
that child's life.

32:08.794 --> 32:10.729
Do you have children?

32:10.762 --> 32:12.498
Yes, I do.

32:12.531 --> 32:14.133
Swear on their lives.

32:16.135 --> 32:18.537
Swear that God sent you.

32:26.778 --> 32:31.050
I swear on my children's
lives that God sent me
to answer your prayer.

32:31.083 --> 32:33.219
And are you free of sin?

32:33.252 --> 32:34.953
No.

32:34.987 --> 32:37.990
Then how could you
have been sent by God?

32:38.024 --> 32:40.326
I renounce my sin.

32:40.359 --> 32:42.294
Swear it.

32:54.973 --> 32:57.043
God,

32:57.943 --> 33:00.112
I renounce my sin.

33:00.146 --> 33:04.550
I am most heartily sorry
for having rejected you.

33:04.583 --> 33:07.219
And you accept Jesus?

33:07.253 --> 33:09.355
Do you accept him?

33:11.057 --> 33:13.192
Tell me.

33:15.327 --> 33:17.463
I accept him
with all my heart.

33:19.565 --> 33:21.533
[ Door Opens ]

33:25.471 --> 33:28.340
Then there's one question
that I must ask you.

33:31.077 --> 33:33.179
[ Whispers ]

33:53.132 --> 33:55.201
Tell me where the baby is.

34:00.472 --> 34:02.374
[ Whispers ]

34:13.552 --> 34:15.487
[ Whispers ]

34:16.588 --> 34:18.424
[ Clinking ]

34:20.192 --> 34:22.428
Ma'am,
come with us, please.

34:22.461 --> 34:24.296
This way.

34:25.964 --> 34:28.300
[ Chatter On Police Radio ]

34:31.770 --> 34:33.772
That way.

34:33.805 --> 34:36.408
[ Chattering ]

34:42.481 --> 34:44.616
[ Crying ]

35:20.986 --> 35:23.121
[ Chatter On Police Radio ]

35:28.126 --> 35:30.229
I'll get my jacket.

35:36.935 --> 35:41.607
Cool Breeze. Don't fire
unless he fires first.

35:41.640 --> 35:43.909
You do not have a shot
unless Whiplash shoots first.

35:43.942 --> 35:45.043
Roger.

35:45.076 --> 35:47.179
Breach in 60.

35:47.213 --> 35:49.581
Sam, let's get you out of there.
Just stand up,

35:49.615 --> 35:52.951
walk to the door
and open it.
[ Sam ] Sure, Jonas.

35:52.984 --> 35:57.022
I walk to the door
and open it,
and Bob bags me.

35:57.055 --> 35:59.458
No. I'll call him off.

35:59.491 --> 36:01.527
It's nice of you
to say anyway.

36:03.462 --> 36:05.531
I wanted to earn
your respect.

36:05.564 --> 36:08.367
- You had it.
- I let you down.

36:09.268 --> 36:11.036
I'm sorry.

36:11.069 --> 36:12.871
You forgive me?

36:12.904 --> 36:16.542
- Ask me in the car.
- I can't go to prison.

36:16.575 --> 36:19.678
A soldier takes responsibility
for his actions.
Respect that.

36:22.348 --> 36:24.383
You do what you gotta do,
Snake Doc.

36:24.416 --> 36:27.519
It was a pleasure
having served with you.

36:43.001 --> 36:43.969
[ Car Alarms Blaring ]

36:45.771 --> 36:47.706
No grenade blast.

36:47.739 --> 36:49.941
[ Man Speaks, Indistinct ]
Move, move, move!

36:51.777 --> 36:54.680
[ Breathing Heavily ]

36:58.116 --> 36:59.951
I can't even do that.

37:01.253 --> 37:03.689
[ Sam Grunts ]

37:07.092 --> 37:09.127
[ Groans ]

37:09.160 --> 37:11.096
[ Coughs ]

37:11.129 --> 37:13.231
[ Car Alarms Blaring ]

37:48.800 --> 37:53.339
She told me I carved
my initials here so I'd be
sure God remembered me.

37:53.372 --> 37:56.107
Is that why you carved them?

37:56.141 --> 37:58.410
Didn't seem so at the time.

37:58.444 --> 38:03.915
- How did it seem at the time?
- It seemed as if
I was defying God.

38:10.989 --> 38:14.660
What did she ask you
before she gave up the baby?

38:17.128 --> 38:19.064
She asked me
for a pledge.

38:20.198 --> 38:22.300
What was the pledge?

38:23.669 --> 38:27.105
I told her God
sent me here...

38:27.138 --> 38:29.040
so I could help her.

38:30.275 --> 38:32.544
Could it be true?

38:33.912 --> 38:35.781
What was the pledge?

38:37.683 --> 38:40.786
- We're locking up the church.
- Yes. Thank you.

39:05.411 --> 39:07.679
[ Groans Softly ]

39:15.286 --> 39:17.556
Just my opinion,
but "don't ask, don't tell"
don't work.

39:17.589 --> 39:20.191
I would have used
the team's women's
locker room, but--

39:20.225 --> 39:21.993
Hasn't been built yet.

39:24.095 --> 39:26.432
[ Refrigerator Door Opens ]

39:26.465 --> 39:29.267
Just so you know,

39:29.300 --> 39:31.670
locals have him in custody
until he can be
transferred to us.

39:31.703 --> 39:34.673
- Good.
- He's being debriefed
right now.

39:34.706 --> 39:37.476
- He says he'll plead guilty.
- He is guilty.

39:41.480 --> 39:44.816
He surprised us all.
Mm-hmm.

39:44.850 --> 39:47.185
[ Bottle Cap Rattles ]
What a waste.

39:47.218 --> 39:48.987
Yes.

39:53.224 --> 39:55.627
You're back on duty.
I keep my commitments,
Sergeant Major.

39:55.661 --> 39:57.629
Yeah, well, you do that.

39:57.663 --> 40:01.600
Floss after meals, vote
the straight ticket, and
I'm sure you'll go to heaven.

40:11.810 --> 40:14.045
Well, now we've done it.
[ Sighs ]

40:14.079 --> 40:16.014
We just bought a house.

40:17.282 --> 40:19.117
Well, you know what?
I was wrong.

40:19.150 --> 40:21.653
This house is exactly
the size it should be.

40:22.621 --> 40:25.356
What's that look?
What look?

40:25.390 --> 40:27.392
You're smiling
like a baby angel.

40:27.425 --> 40:29.394
You like it out here
that much?

40:29.427 --> 40:31.396
I do,
but that's not why.

40:31.429 --> 40:33.499
Why?

40:33.532 --> 40:35.967
'Cause I love you.
That's why.

40:36.001 --> 40:37.903
[ Chuckles ]

40:40.071 --> 40:42.641
What was that pledge
she asked you to make?

40:45.076 --> 40:47.145
Let's take a walk.

40:47.178 --> 40:49.648
** [ Soft Rock ]

40:52.851 --> 40:54.786
[ Chuckles ]

40:57.222 --> 40:59.090
** [ Continues ]

41:01.192 --> 41:04.329
* Does anybody know
where we're really gonna go *

41:04.362 --> 41:07.966
* I was wondering
if we've got that real soul *

41:07.999 --> 41:11.570
* You know, the thing
you cannot trade
or ever own *

41:11.603 --> 41:13.705
[ Refrigerator Door Opens ]

